The usual reading in amicis cannot be correct3 for what need had J ugurtha dando et pol- licitando multa to gain him over, who was already on his side? Per- fecit is a strong word, showing, in my opinion, that Jugurtha had some trouble to conciliate him. Had he been his friend, what wonder- ful or strange thing was it, eum accuratissime recipere ?-C.
